claim.claim-text:
An ex-vivo method of producing an enriched cell population comprising the steps of:
plating a heterogeneous population of nucleus pulposus cells in a media at low cell density;
growing the cells under conditions that inhibit cell attachment;
selecting free-floating in vitro spherical structures comprising disc stem cells, disc progenitor cells, or a mixture thereof;
thereby producing an enriched cell population.

An ex-vivo method of producing an artificial disc, comprising:
(a) isolating a discosphere;
(b) combining the discosphere with a disc scaffold;
(c) growing discospheres in the disc scaffold in a media containing serum;
thereby producing an artificial disc.
